nction of galaxies. The cross-correlation amplitude of mass-defined voids versus mass has a more gentle behaviour remaining negative at larger distances. The cross- to auto-correlation function ratio as a function of the distance normalized to the void radius shows a small scatter around a relation that depends only on the object used to define the voids (galaxies or haloes for instance). The distortion pattern observed in ξ(σ, π) is that of an elongation along the line of sight that extends out to large separations. Positive ξ contours evidence finger-of-god motions at the void walls. Elongations along the line of sight are roughly comparable between galaxy-, halo- and mass-defined voids.},
	urldate = {2022-11-28},
	journal = {MNRAS},
	author = {Padilla, N. D. and Ceccarelli, L. and Lambas, D. G.},
	month = nov,
	year = {2005},
